items.description:
CONTEXT: Instead of returning a single scalar prediction, return the per-tier breakdown. The UI will use this for both casual and quant views.

GOAL: Build a Postgres function predict_place(user_id uuid, place_id uuid) returning jsonb with:
{
  tiers: {
    google:    { rating, count },
    reviewers: { rating: null, count: 0 },  // populated in v0.8
    circle:    { rating, count, contributors: [{friend_id, rating, weight}] }
  },
  prediction: { rating, confidence },
  spread: { circle_vs_google },
  tag: 'consensus' | 'hidden-gem' | 'tourist-trap' | 'unknown' | null  // tag classifier arrives in v0.9; null for now
}

CIRCLE TIER MATH: precision-weighted average of friends' entries on this place, where weight = effective_trust (from v_effective_trust) squared. Include only accepted friends. Weight by place_categories intersecting the entries.

GOOGLE TIER: read from place_external_aggregates (see separate item).
